node.text:
This #WorldChimpanzeeDay, we want to honor our beloved colleague, Joseph Thomas, who passed away in January of 2021 💔

Joseph was a friend, mentor, and respected leader who cared for our rescued chimpanzees at HSI’s Second Chance Chimpanzee Refuge Liberia for over 40 years.

His incredible legacy will continue to live on. Thank you, Joseph Thomas, from the bottom of our hearts, for your strength, determination, and devotion to these chimpanzees. You will always remain an inspiration to us 🙏

node.title: A Lifelong Bond: Memorial to Joseph Thomas

node.text:
South Korean musician, Annie Ko @lovexstereo, was a translator for HSI during the shutdown of a dog meat farm. Little did she know that she would end up adopting one of the rescue pups named DeeJay! 🐾

We are working tirelessly to fight the dog meat trade across Asia but change only manifests when it comes from within the hearts and minds of locals like Annie. The majority of South Koreans are against the dog meat industry and with their support and activism, the end to this trade is in sight.

Together, we can and are making a difference for animals in Asia! ❤

Chewbacca spent his entire life suffering in a muddy pen on a South Korean dog meat farm before being rescued by HSI. Little did this sweet boy know that he would end up being adopted by HSI President, Jeffrey Flocken! 💚

Fast forward to today, and Chewbacca has healed from the pain of his past. His days are filled with constant love, long walks, sleepy naps, and car rides for tasty treats!

Chewbacca means the world to Jeff and his family, and we couldn’t have saved him without your support! THANK YOU for giving dogs, like Chewbacca, a reason to wag their tails! 🐾

node.title: HSI President Adopts South Korean Rescue Dog!

node.text: 🚨 BREAKING: Our Animal Rescue and Response team has identified a dog meat farm in South Korea. With your help, we will be able to save 60+ dogs from being slaughtered for meat. These dogs have lived their entire lives in cages, never setting their paws on solid ground, with inadequate food and water. Together with our local partner, LIFE, we are working to bring these dogs to safety. Donate NOW to help rescue them and protect animals from cruelty worldwide! (Link in bio)

node.text: This #WorldLionDay, and every day, say NO to cruel attractions that breed lions for profit. Lions should be in the wild, not used as props for your selfie or confined for your entertainment. We commend the South African Minister of Environment for her proposed policy to end this exploitative industry. ❌🦁

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Humane Society International on August 05, 2021. May be an image of elephant and nature.

node.text:
African elephants are at risk of extinction in the next few decades. Why? LEGAL markets encourage ILLEGAL poaching to meet the demand for elephant ivory, killing as many as 35,000 elephants each year 😔

It’s time to close ALL legal markets for elephant ivory—and Canada is up next! Urge Canada to save elephants NOW (link in bio) 💔🐘

node.text:
DISASTER RESPONSE: Last week, Henan province in China suffered catastrophic floods after fighting its biggest rainfall in recorded history. HSI responded by funding a team of activists to assist the massive rescue effort in the disaster area of Zhengzhou and donated one ton of pet food.

Together with our China partner group, Vshine, HSI helped dispatch relief goods to thousands of animal victims in some 40 facilities. Dogs and cats, including those saved from the meat trade, were stranded and starving after shelters were covered by floodwater and thick mud.

HSI’s partner groups Vshine and CAWA are still working around the clock caring for injured animals and cleaning up shelters. HSI will continue to monitor the situation and provide further assistance where needed 🙏
